## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date and comprehensive data. Some sources may have biases, and the rapidly evolving nature of COVID-19 research means that new findings could alter current understandings. Additionally, the reliance on publicly available information may not capture all scientific studies or internal health authority data.